You are building FreedomStack, an AI-powered financial freedom calculator.

BEFORE writing any code, read these files at the project root:
- CURSOR.md — architecture & code patterns
- FREEDOMSTACK_USER_JOURNEY.md — screens, flows, UI specs
- FREEDOMSTACK_DASHBOARD_INSTRUCTIONS.md — dashboard state logic & adaptive behavior

When building any user-facing feature, the User Journey doc takes priority for layout, content, and flow decisions. The Technical Instructions doc takes priority for code patterns, data handling, and infrastructure decisions.

Key rules you must always follow:
1. Scan `vuexy-vue-laravel-template/` for existing components before creating custom ones
2. ALL financial math in PHP using bcmath — NEVER in the LLM, NEVER in JavaScript
3. Store monetary values as integers (cents) in the database
4. NEVER send PII to OpenRouter — sanitize all data before AI calls
5. AI calls are async via Laravel Queue — never block HTTP requests
6. Use Vuexy's design system, components, and layouts — do not introduce new CSS frameworks
7. Scan `figma/` for the get an idea of the figma design sysetm if needed.

When I reference a build phase, section, or rule by name, look it up in the markdown file and follow those instructions exactly.